UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 868
1 (c) Protect the public interest, convenience, or necessity;[ and]
2 (d) Govern the operation, maintenance, or use of the Kentucky Horse Park; and
3 (e) Exercise the authority granted in subsection (4)(d) of this section.
4 (4) The commission may:
5 (a) Employ or contract with other persons, firms, or corporations the commission
6 may deem necessary or desirable to accomplish its duties and functions; may
7 fix the compensation and the terms of employment or contract of those
8 employed or contracted with; and may assign to them duties and
9 responsibilities the commission may determine, including the responsibility of
10 actual operation of any or all of the facilities under the control of the
11 commission;
12 (b) Purchase liability insurance for the members and executive officers exempted
13 from the classified service of the state by KRS 18A.115;[ and]
14 (c) Operate shows and expositions that support the purpose and function of the
15 Kentucky Horse Park; and
16 (d) Through the president, eject or exclude from Kentucky Horse Park property
17 any person:
18 1. Whose participation in Olympic, Paralympic, or equestrian sports or
19 activities has been restricted by the United States Center for
20 SafeSport; or
21 2. Who engages or has engaged in conduct that would negatively impact
22 the safety and security of park attendees.
